## 6. Leave Management System

### 6a. Database Tables
```sql
CREATE TABLE leave_applications (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  leave_id VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  school_id VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  employee_id VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  employee_name VARCHAR(255),
  reason TEXT NOT NULL,
  leave_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,   -- paid, unpaid, medical, casual
  from_date DATE NOT NULL,
  to_date DATE NOT NULL,
  status VARCHAR(50) DEFAULT 'pending',  -- pending, approved, rejected
  approved_by VARCHAR(255),
  salary_impact VARCHAR(50),         -- full_deduct, partial, no_deduct
  deduct_percent DECIMAL(5,2) DEFAULT 0,
  pdf_url TEXT,
  notes TEXT,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

### 6b. Backend Routes (`routes/leave.rs` — new file)
- `POST /api/leave/:schoolId` — employee applies for leave
- `GET /api/leave/:schoolId` — list all leave applications
- `GET /api/leave/:schoolId/employee/:empId` — employee's leaves
- `PUT /api/leave/:schoolId/:leaveId/approve` — approve leave (generate PDF letter)
- `PUT /api/leave/:schoolId/:leaveId/reject` — reject
- `PUT /api/leave/:schoolId/:leaveId/extend` — extend dates
- `PUT /api/leave/:schoolId/:leaveId/reduce` — reduce dates
- `GET /api/leave/:schoolId/:leaveId/letter` — download PDF leave letter

### 6c. PDF Leave Letter (auto-generate)
Contents: Employee ID, Name, Reason, Period (from→to), Approved By, Leave Type, Salary Impact

### 6d. Frontend
- Leave application form (employee self-service or admin-initiated)
- Admin leave management table with approve/reject/extend/reduce actions
- Download letter button

